# Legacy ryx Reference (Not a Template)

`docs/ryx/` and `beeantmobile-main/projects/ryx` document the **old 融易行 app** for migration and domain understanding only.

## Do not adopt from legacy

- **Tech stack** — Angular 12, Ionic, Capacitor, Nx beeant layout, `CoreHelper`, global singletons
- **Architecture** — Feature modules tied to `projects/core`, Beeant service patterns, copy-paste page structure
- **Coding style** — Legacy naming, large god services (`TmcService`), jQuery-era assets, inline styles from design cqw
- **UI / UX** — Layout, visuals, interaction patterns; legacy UI quality is below our target

Implement in **this monorepo** using: React + Vite, `apps/h5` / `apps/web`, `@ryx/ui`, `@ryx/api`, `@ryx/shared-types`, and rules under `.cursor/rules/`.

## What legacy is good for

| Use                                                        | Do not use                |
| ---------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------- |
| Business flows (login, flight/hotel/train booking, orders) | Implementation approach   |
| API Method names and request/response shapes               | Client architecture       |
| Route / page inventory for migration matrix                | Component or styling code |
| Edge cases and product behavior notes                      | Code quality as a model   |

## When migrating a feature

1. Read legacy behavior and `docs/api/H5-RYX-MIGRATION.md` for **what** to build.
2. Design against **current** monorepo patterns (hooks, shared API, shadcn/ui, design tokens).
3. Never port legacy files verbatim; rewrite with tests and typecheck passing.

If legacy and monorepo conventions conflict, **always follow monorepo conventions**.
